        We Saw<br>
        The Gap.<br>
        Nobody<br>
        <em>Was</em> Filling It.
      </h2>
      <div>
        <p class="os-problem-body">
          Two options existed in the detailing market: overpriced brands charging $40 for a towel with a logo, or cheap bulk packs that scratch your paint after three uses. Nothing in between.
        </p>
        <br>
        <p class="os-problem-body">
          Founded by <strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.9)">Antanas Kubilius and Jacob Klepacki</strong>, Polaris Car Care was built to fill that exact gap — professional-grade performance at a price that doesn't require a justification. Not the cheapest. Not the most expensive. The most honest.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="os-problem-grid">
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%} ── HOW WE BUILT IT ── {%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="os-diagram bp-bg os-fade">
    <div class="os-section-annotation">02 — How We Built It</div>

    <h2 class="os-diagram-heading">
      Built by Enthusiasts.<br>
      <span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);">Tested in the</span><br>
      Real World.
    </h2>

    <div class="os-steps">
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">01</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">The Idea</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">One founder on brand strategy and operations. One with hands-on professional detailing experience with exotic and luxury vehicles. Different roles, same obsession with quality.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">02</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">Real Testing</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">Every product gets tested on the founders' own vehicles first. If it doesn't perform at that level, it never gets listed. No exceptions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">03</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">Community Review</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">Before anything hits the store, it goes to trusted detailers and enthusiasts in our community. Real feedback from real people who care about their paint.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">04</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">Honest Pricing</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">We price from the customer backward — what performance do you need, and what's fair? We don't inflate margins to fund a lifestyle brand aesthetic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="os-stamp-wrap">
      <div class="os-stamp-quote">
        "Our goal isn't to be the cheapest brand.<br>
        <span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.48);">It's to be the most honest one."</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-stamp">
        <span class="os-stamp-text">REAL WORLD</span>
        <span class="os-stamp-text--big">TESTED</span>
        <span class="os-stamp-text">✓ APPROVED</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%} ── THE STANDARD ── {%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="os-standard bp-bg os-fade">
    <div class="os-section-annotation">03 — The Standard</div>

    <div class="os-standard-grid">
      <div class="os-standard-left">
        <h2 class="os-standard-heading">
          If It Doesn't Pass<br>
          <span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);">Jacob's Test.</span><br>
          It Doesn't Ship.
        </h2>
        <p class="os-standard-body">
          Jacob Klepacki spent years working alongside professional detailers servicing exotic and luxury vehicles. That experience is the baseline. When he evaluates a product, he's not comparing it to the Amazon shelf — he's comparing it to what professionals actually use. Every Polaris product clears that bar before it ever gets near a customer.
        </p>
        {% if section.settings.standard_photo != blank %}
          <div class="os-standard-photo-wrap">
            <img src="{{ section.settings.standard_photo | image_url: width: 900 }}" alt="Product testing" loading="lazy">
          </div>
        {% endif %}
      </div>

      <div class="os-standard-right">
        <div class="os-checklist-label">Quality Control Checklist</div>
        <div class="os-checklist">
          <div class="os-check-item os-check--pass">
            <span class="os-check-mark">✓</span>
            <div>
              <div class="os-check-name">Absorbency</div>
              <div class="os-check-desc">Must pull water without streaking or smearing across paint</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="os-check-item os-check--pass">
